      <accessrestrict id="aspace_6e3953ad4fdd9050ae755f1f0a040ac1">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research. Original audiovisual materials, as well as preservation and duplicating masters, may not be played. Researchers must consult use copies, or if none exist must pay for a use copy, which is retained by the repository. Researchers wishing to obtain an additional copy for their personal use should consult Copying Services information on the Manuscripts and Archives web site.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_3c45a3d2b4d582c7685c13b931419ed3">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>Collection consists of 16mm motion picture film <emph render="italic">Colossal Keepsake</emph> which documents the creation and gifting to Yale University of "Lipstick (Ascending) on Caterpillar Tracks" sculpture by Claes Oldenburg.  The film was shot in 1969 by Peter Hentschel and William Richardson, graduate students at the Yale School of Architecture.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
  
